---
title: Za’atar-Spiced Zucchini & Chicken Sandos with Griddled Onion, Pepper, Sweet Potato Wedges & Harissa Mayo
description: Our chefs have reclaimed the sandwich and now present it to you in a veggie-forward, dinner-worthy form that might change the way you think about sammies... forever. Zucchini and bell pepper are roasted in earthy za’atar spice, then layered between baguettes with pan-seared onion, feta, and a creamy harissa and red pepper aioli. And since we’re thinking outside the box, roasted sweet potato wedges are served up hot on the side. Consider this a victory... in sandwich form!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/638fa359fff3ded81f08d8e8-c339942c.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/654bde6833e04495c0a403d0.pdf
nutrition:
  calories: 1110 kcal
  fat: 53 g
  saturated fat: 15 g
  carbohydrates: 94 g
  sugar: 21 g
  protein: 46 g
  fiber: 9 g
  sodium: 1320 mg
author: HelloFresh
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/zaatar-spiced-zucchini-chicken-sandos-654bde6833e04495c0a403d0
course: main course
time required: 30 minutes
servings: 2
cuisine: Middle East
---

Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @sweet potatoes{2} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Trim and slice @zucchini{1} crosswise on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick rounds. Halve, core, and slice @bell pepper{1} into ½-inch-thick strips. Peel and thinly slice @yellow onion{1} into rounds.

Toss sweet potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{¼%tsp}, @harissa powder{¼%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. (Add a pinch more harissa powder if you like things spicy!)

Toss zucchini and bell pepper on a second baking sheet with a drizzle of @cooking oil{¼%tsp}, @Za'atar spice{1%tbsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast sweet potatoes on top rack and zucchini and bell pepper on middle rack until everything is browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> Zucchini and bell pepper may finish before sweet potatoes; check after 15 minutes and if so, remove from oven and continue roasting sweet potatoes.

While veggies roast, in a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{4%tbsp}, half the @red pepper jam{1%unit}, and @harissa powder{¼%tsp}. (Add more harissa to taste if desired.) Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a large, preferably #nonstick pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken; cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest. Wipe out pan.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a large, preferably nonstick pan over medium-high heat. Add onion rounds and cook, undisturbed, until deeply browned and tender, ~{2-3%minutes} per side. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Halve @demi-baguette{2} lengthwise.

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in pan used for onion over medium heat. Add baguettes, cut sides down, and toast until golden brown, ~{1-3%minutes}.

> Depending on the size of your pan, you may need to toast in batches, using 1 TBSP butter for each batch.

Press @feta cheese{½%cup} into cut sides of bottom buns. Spread cut sides of top buns with harissa mayo (save some for serving). Fill buns with zucchini, bell pepper, and onion.

Divide sandos and sweet potato wedges between plates. Serve with remaining harissa mayo on the side for dipping.

> Slice chicken crosswise. Fill buns with as much chicken as you like along with zucchini, bell pepper, and onion.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.